Why Order This Gig?

questionsAndAnswers.question: What is webflow and how it works?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Webflow is a no-code website builder with easy to use user interface. Without any knowledge of websites or coding, you would be able to 1. Add/remove/modify content, 2. Publish your site on the fly. 3. Supports eCommerce 4. Has a powerful CMS which lets you add new content easily.

questionsAndAnswers.question: How much webflow costs?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Webflow has different pricing tiers. To take your website live you need either Basic or CMS packages usually. They cost about $18/month and $24/month respectively. You can also export the code and use a third-party hosting provider

questionsAndAnswers.question: What I need to have in order to get started?
questionsAndAnswers.answer:
You need to have 
1. Design file in Figma/XD/Sketch/Photoshop. Don't have a design file? Let's connect and discuss.
2. webflow account login credentials (optional).
3.  Assets (like website copy, images, videos etc).

questionsAndAnswers.question: Do you need webflow account login details?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: No, You need to add me to your workspace as a guest developer. Then I will able to access your site.

questionsAndAnswers.question: Do you work on custom orders?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: Yes, If your website doesn't fit into any of my packages, you can create an offer or you can also contact me via inbox and we will discuss your project

questionsAndAnswers.question: Where can I get your portfolio or past work samples?
questionsAndAnswers.answer: You can check my Fiverr for my portfolio. Alternatively, you can also inbox me to inquire about my past work samples.
